obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37152)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37152&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Rehabilitation Finance`
  line `Administration Act, 1948.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `(2) [It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1950, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 18-2-1950).`
  line `2. 1st June, 1948, see Gazette of India, 1948, Extraordinary.`
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37153)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37153&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Act" means the Rehabilitation Finance Administration Act, 1948;`
  line
  line `(b) "Administration" means the Rehabilitation Finance Administration constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "borrower" means an individual, company, association or body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, to whom a loan has been advanced under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "displaced person" means—`
  line
  line `(i) a person who, being displaced from any area ^1`
  line `[now forming part of Pakistan] on account`
  line `of civil disturbances or fear of such disturbances, has settled and is engaged or intends to engage`
  line `in any business or industry in India, or`
  line
  line `(ii) a person in India who, having had his business, industry or property, wholly or partially`
  line ^1
  line `[in any area now forming part of Pakistan], has lost, wholly or partially, such business, industry,`
  line `or property on account of civil disturbances or the fear of such disturbances, and who is engaged,`
  line `or intends to engage in any business or industry in India;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(e) "loan" means a sum of money advanced by the Administration—`
  line
  line `(i) to a displaced person for the purpose of any business or industry in which he is engaged or`
  line `intends to engage himself, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of any business or industry, a substantial portion of which is owned by`
  line `displaced persons; and]`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under section 23 or regulations made under`
  line `section 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1950, s. 3, for "outside India".`
  line `2. Subs. by s.3, ibid., for clause (e).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37154)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 1 of 1950, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37154&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a Corporation`
  line `called the Rehabilitation Finance Administration for giving financial assistance on reasonable terms to`
  line `displaced persons to enable them to settle in business and industry ^1`
  line `[or to any business or industry, a`
  line `substantial portion of which is owned by displaced persons]`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name of the Rehabilitation Finance`
  line `Administration having perpetual succession and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, to acquire, hold and transfer property, both movable and immovable, and shall by the said name`
  line `sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The administration shall have its head office at Delhi and may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, open branches at such places in India as it may consider necessary to discharge`
  line `effectively its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37155)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1950, s. 5, for "three"`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37155&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administration shall consist of the following`
  line `members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government who shall be called the Chief`
  line Administrator;
  line
  line `(b)`
  line ^1
  line `[four] officials appointed by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(c)`
  line ^1
  line `[four] non-officials nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by the Administration shall be called in question on the ground merely of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy or any defect in the constitution of the Administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37156)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37156&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute an Advisory Board to advise the`
  line `Administration on matters of policy and may where necessary constitute a Regional Committee to advice`
  line `each branch of the Administration.`
  line
  line `(2) The Advisory Board shall consist of such members, not exceeding fifteen in number, as may be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37157)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Terms of office of the members of the Administration and the Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37157&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `member appointed under clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4 shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A member nominated under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 4 or sub-section (2) of section`
  line `5 shall hold office for a term of two years from the date of his nomination and shall be eligible for`
  line re-nomination.
  line
  line `(3) A nominated member may resign his membership by writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Central Government and he shall thereupon cease to be a member.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy created by resignation under sub-section (3) or by any other reason shall be`
  line `filled by fresh nomination and the person nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the`
  line `remainder of the term for which the member whose place he takes was nominated.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37158)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Disclosure of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37158&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of the Administration shall have any interest, direct or`
  line `indirect, in any business, industry or concern to which any assistance under section 12 has been given or`
  line `is to be given and if any such member acquires such interest at any time during the continuance of such`
  line `assistance, he shall immediately disclose it to the Administration and shall either resign his membership`
  line `or disclose of his interest in such manner and within such time as he may be directed by it.`
  line
  line `(2) Any member of the Advisory Board who has any interest, director indirect, in any business,`
  line `industry or concern to which any assistance under section 12 has been given or is to be given or acquires`
  line `such interest at any time during the continuance of such assistance shall immediately disclose it to the`
  line `Administration and shall not participate in the proceedings of the Advisory Board relating to such`
  line assistance.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37159)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Removal from membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37159&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6, the Central`
  line `Government may, for any reason which may appear to it to be sufficient, remove any member at anytime`
  line `from the Administration or the Advisory Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37160)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `The Chief Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37160&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Administrator shall be a whole time servant of the`
  line `Administration and shall receive such salaries and allowances and shall be subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be determined by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37161)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Staff.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37161&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Administration may, in the manner prescribed ^1`
  line `* * *,—`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a Deputy Chief Administrator and such other officers and servants as may be required`
  line `to enable it to carry out the functions under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) fix the salary and allowances or other conditions of service of the Deputy Chief`
  line `Administrator, other officers and servants;`
  line
  line `(c) fix the remuneration and allowances payable to the members of the Administration and of the`
  line `Advisory Board:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that the appointment and the fixation of the salary, allowances and other conditions of`
  line `service of the Deputy Chief Administrator and such other officers as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, shall be subject to the previous sanction of that Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and with the prior sanction of the Central Government" omitted by Act 1 of 1950, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Added by s. 6, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37162)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Funds of the Administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37162&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The Central Government may from time to time advance`
  line `money to the Administration for its business, the aggregate amount of which, —`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of enabling the Administration to advance loans, shall not, save as hereinafter`
  line `provided, exceed twelve crores and fifty lakhs of rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of enabling the Administration to meet any liability which it may incur in`
  line `guaranteeing losses in respect of loans advanced by scheduled banks, shall not exceed two crores of`
  line `rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after the lapse of such period from the commencement of this Act as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit to fix in this behalf, any sum of money earmarked for the purpose specified in`
  line `clause (b) is found not to have been actually advanced for that purpose and is not, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, likely to be required for the said purpose, the Central Government may utilize the`
  line `money for making advances from time to time to the Administration for the purposes specified in clause`
  line `(a), and when any such advance is made, the limit specified in clause (a) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `correspondingly increased.]`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line ^2
  line `[Subject to any regulations that may be made in this behalf, all moneys belonging to the`
  line `Administration which are not immediately required by the Administration for any purpose] shall be`
  line `deposited in the Reserve Bank of India or any agents thereof or invested in such securities as may be`
  line `approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administration shall pay interest on the money so advanced at the rate of 3 per cent. per`
  line `annum to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1953, s. 2, for sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1950, s. 7, for "All moneys belonging to the Administration".`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37163)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Business of the Administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1953, s. 3, for section 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37163&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Business of the Administration.—The Administration may—`
  line
  line `(a) subject to the provisions of section 13, advance loans;`
  line
  line `(b) guarantee, on such terms and conditions as may be agreed upon, losses which a scheduled`
  line `bank may suffer in respect of any loan advanced by it and approved by the Administration:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount which may be guaranteed in respect of any scheduled bank and the`
  line `terms and conditions on which such guarantee may be given shall be subject to the prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the maximum liability of the Administration under such guarantee shall not`
  line `exceed the amount for the time being available under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) do all such acts and things as may be incidental to or consequential upon the performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act including the running of the Administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37164)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Loans.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37164&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may prescribe the limits as to amounts within which loans`
  line `may be advanced by the Administration.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of advancing any loan under sub-section (1), the Administration may call for any`
  line `report either through its own staff, or through the District Officer of the district in which the borrower`
  line `resides or carries on business, or through any State ^1`
  line `* * * Government, or through any bank of any other`
  line `appropriate agency.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administration shall charge interest from the borrower at such rate not exceeding`
  line `6 per cent. per annum as may be specified by it.`
  line
  line `(4) The period of the loan shall not exceed ^2`
  line `[fifteen] years.`
  line
  line `(5) The loan may be advanced either for fixed capital or working capital or for both.`
  line
  line `The assets created from the loan shall, notwithstanding any law or usage to the contrary, be deemed`
  line `to be mortgaged to the Administration for the repayment of the loan together with the interest thereon and`
  line `the amount of the loan and the interest thereon shall be first charge on such assets.`
  line
  line `(6) The Administration may also take such further security for any loan as it may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or a State" omitted by Act 36 of 1957, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1953, s. 4, for "ten".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37165)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to call for repayment before agreed period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37165&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any agreement to the`
  line `contrary, the Administration may, by notice, require any borrower forthwith to repay in full with interest`
  line `thereon any loan borrowed from it,—`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Administration that false or misleading information in any material`
  line `particular was given by the borrower for obtaining the loan or while furnishing any information under`
  line `section 17; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the borrower has failed to comply with the terms of the contract with the Administration in`
  line `the matter of the loan; or`
  line
  line `(c) if there is a reasonable apprehension that the borrower is unable to pay his debts or that`
  line `insolvency proceedings or proceedings for liquidation may be commenced against him; or`
  line
  line `(d) if for any other reason it is necessary in the opinion of the Administration to protect the`
  line `interests of the Administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37166)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Mode of recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37166&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If the amount of loan or any instalment thereof or interest thereon which is`
  line `due, in accordance with the terms of the contract or under the provisions of section 14, has not been`
  line `repaid, the Administration may,—`
  line
  line `(a) without prejudice to any other remedy provided by law, recover such loan, instalment or interest`
  line `as arrears of land revenue, or`
  line
  line `(b) take charge of the business or industry of the borrower on such terms and conditions as it may`
  line `deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37167)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 16.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37167&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Accounts and audit.—(1) The Administration shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the profit and loss account and the`
  line `balance-sheet in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Company and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Administration shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor`
  line `General of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by`
  line `the Administration to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Administration shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books,`
  line `accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the`
  line Administration.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Administration as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `or any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid`
  line `before both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37168)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37168&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Administrator or any other Officer authorised by him in`
  line `writing in this behalf may, by order, require any borrower to furnish such information or to produce such`
  line `books of accounts and other documents for inspection at such time and place as may be specified in the`
  line `order and the borrower shall comply with such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Administrator or such officer may inspect such books of account or documents`
  line `produced and take extracts therefrom.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Administrator or the officer making the inspection or any person working under his`
  line `order shall not communicate or allow to be communicated to any person not legally entitled thereto any`
  line `information relating to the affairs of the borrower.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37169)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Returns.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A. O. 1950, for "the Central Legislature".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37169&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administration shall furnish to the Central Government a half-yearly report`
  line `together with accounts and such other information within such time and in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The report shall be laid before ^1`
  line `[Parliament] as soon as may be after it is prepared.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37170)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Central Government to give direction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37170&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, give to the Administration such general or special directions as it`
  line `thinks fit, and the Administration shall, in the exercise of its functions under this Act, comply with any`
  line `such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37171)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Exemption from taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37171&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Income-tax Act,`
  line `1922 (11 of 1922)^1`
  line `, or in any other enactment for the time being in force relating to income-tax, super-tax`
  line `or business profits tax, the Administration shall not be liable to pay any income-tax, super-tax or business`
  line `profits tax or any incomes, profits or gains.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37172)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Liquidation of the Administration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37172&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No provision of law relating to insolvency or to the`
  line `winding up of companies or corporation shall apply to the Administration and the Administration shall`
  line `not be placed in liquidation save by the order of the Central Government and in such manner as it may`
  line direct.
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the Administration being placed in liquidation, the assets of the Administration,`
  line `after meeting the liabilities, if any, shall vest in the Central Government and the Central Government shall`
  line `thereupon have all the powers of the Administration in recovering the loans remaining unpaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (37173)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37173&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Administration may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any`
  line `power or duty which under any of the provisions of this Act is conferred or imposed upon the Administration shall, in such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction,`
  line `be exercised or discharged by the Chief Administrator, Deputy Chief Administrator or any other person`
  line `subordinate to the Administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (37174)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37174&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (37175)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37175&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administration may, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, make regulations, not inconsistent with this Act or the rules made there under, to`
  line `provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such regulation may`
  line `provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions on which a person may be recognised as a displaced person,`
  line
  line `(b) the manner and the time of the general meeting of the Administration, or Advisory Board or`
  line `Regional Committee and the procedure to be followed thereat and the manner in which right of voting`
  line `be exercised,`
  line
  line `(c) the terms on which the Administration may grant loans,`
  line
  line `(d) forms of returns and statements required under this Act,`
  line
  line `(e) the duties and conduct, salaries, allowances and conditions of service of officers, servants and`
  line `agents of the Administration,`
  line
  line `(f) manner and form of application for loans and contracts,`
  line
  line `(g) manner in which accounts of the Administration shall be kept and audited,`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which and the conditions under which the business or industry of a person to`
  line `whom a loan has been advanced may be taken charge of and administered under section 15,`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which has to be or may be specified under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All regulations made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette and shall come`
  line `into force on such date as may be specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (37176)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634&sectionId=37176&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00011_194812_1517807326634
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.—Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.]`
